  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the tandoor grill to 200°C.",
    "In a blender or food processor, blend together coconut milk, coriander seeds, cumin seeds, lemongrass, garlic, chili flakes, soy sauce, tamarind paste, honey, and coconut sugar to make the marinade.",
    "Add the chicken breast to the marinade and mix well to coat.",
    "Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.",
    "Thread the marinated chicken onto skewers, leaving a small space between each piece.",
    "Grill the satay over medium heat for 5-7 minutes per side, or until cooked through.",
    "Transfer the satay to a serving platter and garnish with fresh coriander leaves.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
